cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SI 

The paper focuses on the performance and security analysis of a blockchain technology designed for Internet of Things (IoT) applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a Markov chain model and a stochastic model to analyze the behavior of the blockchain under dynamic load conditions, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
